list.name: Default Changelist
list.comment: Going to make the first roll out from here.

task.summary: Default task
Working on the communications and overtime system
Reset the ot_time to 8 hours
Got some of the 'close state' buttons to work. Color changes are functional. Stay on top hints are active... next up. Figuring out the message system. Need short-term and long term solutions.
The OT system is now sending messages! Now I just have to get it to send the RIGHT message!

Better message with buttons, BUT I still have to get those buttons to work. Also need to add the Actual Entity in there. And lastly, I need to set this up so that it ignores people in the Salary pool.
Got the hourly/salary bit to work, but I have to add more conditions for the Tardis OT launcher, since it's not behaving properly after the first open.

Solved one major problem with Tardis. You have to be clocked in for it to work! Ha ha! In other news: The Auto-Clock-in popup did not appear this morning. I have to debug that. Lunch pop up worked, but again, only if you're clocked in.
Updated regular time_lord from the dev4 project. time_lord_dev3_post.py is the original time_lord with the bugs and shit in it.

Most systems seem to be working, at least rudimentarily. Biggest issues now: UI only partially updates. Primarily the button and drop-downs don't update properly. Lastly, the status lights and output still need to be setup.
I'm still having stupid issues with the update portion of the UI. Furthermore, I'm still getting a lot of freezing up, which is driving me bananas. EOD for today.
Adding an output system for temporary collection of timesheets and such. Also, state of the day for other Time Lord utilityes; where I left off yesterday.
Logging system working
For some reason the graphic elements of the new tool aren't showing up. Not a big deal, but I'd like to get it resolved quickly
Ok. No idea why the resources aren't working for this file. Moving on to the engine for now.
Got the basic Excel outputer to work. Needs some improvement, but it could sell now.
Everything except the background images works! Damned close!
Fixed an errant excess line.
Got the images to work, but now there's a weird error/non-error that doesn't seem to matter, but is showing up anyways.

I am happy with the Alpha Payroll Collector. It seems to be working. Short term future changes may include removing Aaron's ID from the accounting (for their reasons; I'll ask), and finding a clever way to add people who aren't regularly in Shotgun, i.e. Tyler Winther
Have a rudimentary system for sorting and correcting the timesheets and make sure they are copacetic
Starting to get the algorithm to work. Not there yet.
Timesheet comparitor is working, at least preliminarily.
Ok, got the consistency checker working, and I think it's reliable. Only time and data will tell
Integrated consistency check into the cleanup process.
Minor exception handling change
Changed all occurances of "last_timesheet" with "latest_timesheet". Longer, sure, but more accurately descriptive.
Moved the cleanup process to the Tardis. It is set to run every hour.
Converted most of the prints to loggers
Got the init_ui to properly update the UI to the latest timesheet if it doesn't match the saved info. Still have to get the listener to update it as well.

Ok, so I think I need to have an event updater built into the tardis as well. Something to at least make sure that the time_capsule has the most recent TimeLogID burned into it. Anyhow, look into how that data is being accessed, processed and saved.
Last comment for the day. This shit wasn't keeping up. Once the time_capsule was updated, it all ran faster. Thus... that shit needs to stay up to date.
Going to try and restore functionality to the Stream Handler Output Window.
Reintroduced the streaming output handler
Added the cleanup process back into the clock out routine. Required change to continuum to allow variables. Found problem with adding lunch to TS later in the day. Caused negative duration.
Reworked the logging to output better data to the monitor. Now the monitor is a little scary. Need to get the status lights working and then swap the log direction.
Starting the day off by starting to work on the DCC implementation.
Added a check for negative duration. Set to flag the Time Sheet and send a Slack about it.
Updated tld file manually. Part of my hang up seems to be around that process.
Solved an issue that was freezing the UI up quite a lot. Had to do with the listener over-updating the tld file.
Added a messaging system to the TARDIS when it gets closed. Accidentally added a bunch of things to the GIT that I didn't want to.
Start of the week. Beginning the roll-out portion of our quest
Added error comm system to some of the systems.
updated logging interval
Added the coordinators to the comm system
Versioned up and made some notes about PySide2
rolled out the first patch: 0.3.1. Fixed an issue with non-existent timesheets causing the window to not open.
Fixed missing timesheet issue

New subversion. Added versions to all windows. Made some features of the Tardis Admin only. Rearranged Tardis menus. Changed the way the Start of Day launcher works. Noticed it was skipping seconds, so I made something a little more broad scope for time.
made "quit" an admin feature of the Tardis
